<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Some Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>This is a dummy approve page. Press the home button or a link.</h1>

    <p>The dummy functions on the server end are generating MongoDB ids rather than fetching them from the database.</p>
    <p>This page is basically identical to the /archive page, and the two can possibly be merged to avoid redundancy.</p>

    {{#if id}}
    <p>You clicked the link for the form with id: {{id}}</p>
    {{/if}}
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>SAP Number</th>
        <th>Employee Name</th>
        <th>Form ID</th>
        <th>Link</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>{{arrayOfFormIds.[0].SAPNum}}</td>
        <td>{{arrayOfFormIds.[0].name}}</td>
        <td>{{arrayOfFormIds.[0].id}}</td>
        <td><a href="/approve/{{arrayOfFormIds.[0].id}}">Link to Form</a></td>
      </tr>
